        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "I agree with you that this fix is not ideal. Double quotes would be better. The fix for this would need to go into ESLint in this file: https://github.com/eslint/eslint/blob/master/lib/rules/quotes.js It looks like we'd need to take into account the value of the `avoidEscape` rule setting whenever converting between quote types in `--fix`. This seems like a reasonable change.\r\n\r\n@wmhilton As a next step, would you like to open this as an issue on ESLint to see what they think of the idea?",
